Class DummyArgumentType

java.lang.Object
lanat.utils.ErrorsContainerImpl<CustomError>
lanat.ArgumentType<Void>
lanat.argumentTypes.DummyArgumentType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Parseable<Void>, NamedWithDescription, ParentElementGetter<ArgumentType<?>>, ErrorsContainer<CustomError>, Resettable
public final class DummyArgumentType extends ArgumentType<Void>
This is a dummy argument type that does not parse any values. It cannot be instantiated, and it's only purpose is to be used as a default value for the Argument.Define annotation.
